<p>I want to send simple ajax to youtube's oembed:</p>  <pre><code>$.ajax({     url: "https://www.youtube.com/oembed?format=json&amp;url=" + url,     crossDomain: true,     dataType: 'json',     complete: function(res) {         // work with result     } }); </code></pre>  <p>As I understand browser blocks cross domain calls and that's why this call fails.</p>  <p>Is there a way to do it without additional services such as: YQL (<a href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/15949969/get-youtube-oembed-json-with-ajax">get youtube oembed json with ajax</a>) or reembed(<a href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/12929249/oembed-for-youtube">Oembed for youtube</a>) or some server side proxy and just simply send it from js ?</p>